The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves optimization and approximation algorithms (cs.DS), as well as decision making under uncertainty (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on revenue optimization in auctions (cs.EC), which is a common topic in mechanism design. Finally, the paper uses behavioral models to capture buyer risk aversion, which is a topic in machine learning and decision making (cs.LG).
